Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.26,0:01:42.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,Septiembre
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.44,0:01:51.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,Este es el árbol del que te hablé.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.24,0:01:52.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Finales de Septiembre
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.61,0:01:54.02,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Estamos a finales de Septiembre.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.02,0:01:59.00,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,He venido con mi hermana, Araragi Karen,\N al dojo al que ella va.{I had come with my sister, Araragi Karen, to the dojo that she frequented.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.68,0:02:05.35,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, realmente es un árbol.{Well, it really is a tree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.33,0:02:08.10,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es difícil de ignorar.{Tiene bastante presencia.}{It has a pretty alluring presence.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.75,0:02:09.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Seguro que eso es cierto?{Is it true?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.77,0:02:14.25,HnF,,0,0,0,,El hecho de que este árbol está aquí, \Ny nadie se ha dado cuenta.{The fact that this tree was here and apparently, nobody had realized it until now.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.39,0:02:18.90,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Recordemos de nuevo la historia.{Let’s rewind the story again.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.67,0:02:23.08,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Estaba solo en mi habitación, estudiando para los exámenes de entrada. {I was alone in my room, studying for entrance exams.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.29,0:02:28.33,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hey, ¡aquí están las tetas que te gustan tanto!{Hey, Nii-chan. It’s the boobs you love so much!}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.48,0:02:32.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué pasa? ¿Necesitas algo, Karen?{What is it. Do you need something, Karen-chan?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.02,0:02:36.28,HnF,,0,0,0,,Buena pregunta, pero no la adecuada.{A very good question, but not an appropriate one.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.37,0:02:40.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,La pregunta correcta sería: '¿Cuándo deberíamos ir?'{The correct question to be asked is, ‘When should we go?’, you see.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.42,0:02:45.01,HnF,,0,0,0,,No asumas que he dicho que voy a ayudarte, y que voy a ir contigo a algún sitio.{Don’t talk with the assumption that I’ve agreed to help you and I’m going to accompany you somewhere.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.01,0:02:50.31,HnF,,0,0,0,,Quita tus enormes pechos de mi cabeza, y respóndeme.{Take your enormous chest off my head right now and answer my question.}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.31,0:02:51.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Necesitas algo?{Do you need something?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.66,0:02:57.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,Vamos a ver, sí que necesito algo. Y acabo de decírtelo, ¿no?{Let’s see, do I need something. But you already know what it is, don’t you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.15,0:03:02.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Vale, no digas nada más. \N¡Tan solo quítame de encima tus enormes pechos!{Okay, you don’t need to say anything. Just take off your enormous chest,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.41,0:03:04.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Tus enormes pechos!{your enormous chest!}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.67,0:03:07.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, me rendiré por esta vez.{Fine. I’ll surrender this time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.04,0:03:12.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque los haya llamado enormes,{Well, even if I called it enormous,}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.50,0:03:13.66,HnF,,0,0,0,,no llegan al nivel de los de Hanekawa.{It was hardly on the level of Hanekawa’s.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.92,0:03:16.67,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora, no toques mucho las tetas de tu hermana.{Now, don’t touch your sister’s boobs so much, Nii-chan.}{hermana, hermano... xD}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.67,0:03:19.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,A cambio de eso, vas a tener que escucharme.{In return for that, you’ll have you listen to what I have to say.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.00,0:03:27.75,HnF,,0,0,0,,No sé qué te habrá contado Tsukihi,\N pero no tiene que ver conmigo ¿verdad?{I don’t know what you heard from Tsukihi-chan, but in this case none of it has anything to do with me, all right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.53,0:03:31.86,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tú eres la única que se está aprovechando injustamente de mí.{You’re the one who’s arbitrarily taking advantage of me in both ways, all right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:35.23,HnF,,0,0,0,,Nunca pensé que dirías que es injusto.{I never thought you would say it was arbitrary.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.23,0:03:41.70,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensé que en vez de 'la honestidad es lo mejor',\N dirías 'las tetas son lo mejor'.{I thought that instead of 'honesty is the best policy’, it was \N'boobs are the best policy’ for you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.70,0:03:46.48,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por favor, no me apliques ese proverbio de esa manera, Karen.{Please don’t apply a proverb to me in such a nonsensical way, Karen-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.58,0:03:50.22,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Entonces qué quieres? {So what is it? Tell me already.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.40,0:03:53.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Quieres que te lo diga?\N Supongo que no tengo otra opción.{You want me to tell you? I guess I have no choice.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:56.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,La verdad es, que necesito que me ayudes.{The truth is, I want you to help me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.86,0:04:01.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Dios mío. Karen, es imposible para la gente ayudar a otras personas.{Dear me. Karen-chan, it’s impossible for people to help other people.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.42,0:04:04.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Uno solo puede ayudarse por sí mismo.{One can only choose to be helped on their own}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.44,0:04:08.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,No me digas todas esas tonterías, o te pegaré.{Don’t spew out such meaningless nonsense at me or I’ll punch you,}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.04,0:04:13.98,HnF,,0,0,0,,Deja de decir todas esas cosas aburridas\N y escucha lo que tengo que decir, idiota.{Stop saying all that boring stuff and listen to what I have to say, you idiot.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.05,0:04:16.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Quieres que te dé de verdad?{Want me to beat you up a bit?}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.98,0:04:18.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,Vale, te escucharé.{All right, I’ll listen.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.24,0:04:23.32,HnF,,0,0,0,,Te voy a escuchar, así que date prisa.{I’ll listen, so spit it out already. Quickly.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.14,0:04:28.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Gracias hermano, ¡estoy feliz!{Thank you, nii-chan, I’m so happy!}
