Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.16,0:04:48.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,Además, no voy a hacerte nada.{ And I’m not going to feel you up!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.05,0:04:52.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si no quieres convertirte en un personaje intratable,\N céntrate en lo que sea que quieras decir.{If you don’t want me to become the taciturn kind of character, then talk about whatever it is already!}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:53.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es sobre un árbol.{It’s about a tree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:59.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,Se ha descubierto un árbol en nuestro dojo,\N y todos lo tratan como si fuera una molestia.{A tree was discovered at our dojo, and everyone else is treating it as if it was in the way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.27,0:05:05.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es por eso que quiero hacer algo. \NPero no soy capaz.{That’s why I want to do something. But I don’t have that kind of power, Nii-chan.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.60,0:05:06.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Ayúdame!{¡Haz algo!}{So you do something!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:12.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué? ¿No lo entiendes? Eres estúpido.{What, you don’t get it? You really are dense, nii-chan.}{denso se utiliza en españa?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.50,0:05:14.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Se ha descubierto un árbol en tu dojo?{A tree was discovered at your dojo?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:19.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Te refieres a esos tablones de madera que rompes en kárate?{Um, do you mean those wooden boards that you break in karate?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.11,0:05:20.13,HnF,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.70,0:05:25.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Hay un patio detrás del dojo,\N y he descubierto el árbol ahí.{There’s a yard behind the dojo. And, we discovered a tree there!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.74,0:05:29.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo que no entiendo es que qué quieres decir con que lo has encontrado.{And what I’m not getting is what you mean by you discovered it…}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:33.72,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Cómo si descubrieras algunas ramas rotas en el suelo o algo?{Like, you discovered some branches that had fallen in the backyard or something?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.86,0:05:37.31,HnF,,0,0,0,,No entiendes nada, ¿verdad?{You really don’t understand anything, do you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.31,0:05:39.11,HnF,,0,0,0,,Nunca dije nada de eso.{I never said anything about that.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:43.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es porque solo te interesa mirarme las tetas. {las tetas que estás mirando.}{It’s because all you think about are boobs that your eyes are looking at.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.78,0:05:44.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,No estoy mirando,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.90,0:05:50.58,HnF,,0,0,0,,y de todas formas, lo único en lo que estoy pensando, es en las preocupaciones de mi hermana.{I’m not looking, and regardless, all that’s in my head right now is concern for my sister!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.90,0:05:53.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Gracias por preocuparte por mí.{Thanks for being so concerned for me!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.42,0:05:54.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo escucha lo que le interesa.{She really only listens to the good things}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.85,0:05:58.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,No son romas rotas, ni tablones de madera.{It’s not branches. And it’s not boards to break either.}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.21,0:06:01.12,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es un árbol creciendo, con sus raíces.{It’s a growing tree. A tree with roots in the ground!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:04.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Todavía no lo entiendes?{No? Do you still not get it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.14,0:06:06.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,Déjame pensar, Karen.{Let me think this through, Karen-chan}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.63,0:06:11.05,HnF,,0,0,0,,Básicamente, en el dojo al que vas,\N hay un árbol creciendo...{Basically, in the backyard of the dojo you go to, a tree was growing…}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:16.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y no te has dado cuenta de que estaba creciendo ahí.{and you hadn’t noticed that it had been growing there?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.39,0:06:18.89,HnF,,0,0,0,,No solo yo, nadie lo había visto.{It’s not just me! It was everybody!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:25.40,HnF,,0,0,0,,Incluyendo mi profesor, todos se dieron cuenta hace poco que estaba ese árbol ahí.{Including my master, who owns the dojo, everyone noticed just recently that a tree was there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.40,0:06:28.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, el otro día, lo descubrí.{So, the other day, I discovered it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.26,0:06:33.41,HnF,,0,0,0,,Fue un gran problema,\N porque nadie se había dado cuenta.{It was a huge incident because nobody had noticed.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.41,0:06:41.96,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Eh? ¿Alguien lo plantó por la noche? Todos estábamos hablando sobre eso.{Eh? What’s this? Did someone plant it here overnight? We were all talking about it, and it was really rowdy.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:46.71,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero ya sabes, da un poco de miedo.{But, you know… It’s kind of scary.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.71,0:06:49.59,HnF,,0,0,0,,Después de usar ese patio\N para entrenar y esas cosas,{Despite using that backyard for all this time for training and stuff,}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.59,0:06:54.09,HnF,,0,0,0,,que nadie se haya dado cuenta de que había un árbol ahí...{nobody ever noticed that a tree had been growing there.}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.56,0:06:58.02,HnF,,0,0,0,,Eso es exactamente.{That’s exactly it, onii-chan!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.02,0:07:02.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo que todo el mundo está diciendo. Da miedo.{That’s what everyone else is saying! That it’s scary.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.27,0:07:04.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, no es miedo,\N es más como extraño o algo así.{Well, not scary, more like ominous or something.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.90,0:07:07.78,HnF,,0,0,0,,Obviamente el profesor no dijo nada de eso,{Obviously Master doesn’t say anything like that,}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:11.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero mis compañeros están como con escalofríos.{but my less disciplined seniors and juniors are, like, getting the shivers and stuff!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.14,0:07:18.24,HnF,,0,0,0,,El hecho de que había un árbol creciendo sin que lo notases, ¿no es extraño para ti?{So the fact that the tree had been growing without you noticing wasn’t ominous to you?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.24,0:07:19.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,No.{Nope.}{Supernecesario dejar el ingles ahi}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.46,0:07:22.46,HnF,,0,0,0,,Estaba sorprendida, pero no asustada.{I was surprised, but I wasn’t scared.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:29.63,HnF,,0,0,0,,Más bien, como alumna, es vergonzoso que no me haya dado cuenta todavía de algo como eso.{Rather, as a martial artist, it’s almost embarrassing that I never noticed something like that after all this time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.63,0:07:32.82,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es tan vergonzoso que podría matarme a mí misma.{It’s so embarrassing I could almost kill myself!}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.82,0:07:34.98,HnF,,0,0,0,,Tu mentalidad de alumna es muy débil.{Your martial artist mentality is way too weak.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.58,0:07:41.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pensé que todo el mundo se sentiría igual, pero no.{I thought everyone else would feel the same way, but I was wrong.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.44,0:07:44.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Nadie se sintió así.{Since nobody felt that way}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.54,0:07:49.96,HnF,,0,0,0,,Dijeron que por el miedo que da, lo van a talar.{They said because it’s scary, they’re going to chop it down.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.67,0:07:57.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,No nos dimos cuenta \Nporque no prestamos atención suficiente.{We never noticed because we weren’t paying attention.}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:05.21,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y cuando por fin nos percatamos, \Ndijimos que era extraño y decidimos talarlo.{And once we finally notice it, we say it’s ominous and want to chop it down.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.21,0:08:06.76,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿No te parece sin sentido?{Isn’t that unreasonable?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.13,0:08:14.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Así que, básicamente, quieres que el tema se zanje de alguna manera, sin que el árbol sea talado, ¿no?{So basically, what you want to do is settle this somehow to keep this tree from being chopped down, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:21.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí, lo que quiero es que este árbol se quede aquí para siempre, tal y como está ahora.{Yeah, So what I want is for this tree to stay here forever, just the way it is.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.58,0:08:24.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,Para siempre...{Forever, huh…}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:31.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ya lo tengo. Karen, no dudes en contar con tu confiable hermano.{ I got it. Karen-chan, feel free to rely on your reliable brother.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.64,0:08:34.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Qué planeas hacer exactamente?{What are you specifically planning on doing?}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:37.26,HnF,,0,0,0,,Algo haré.{I’ll do something.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:40.60,HnF,,0,0,0,,Haz algo, ¡Hanekawa!{Do something, Hanekawa!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.96,0:08:42.34,HnF,,0,0,0,,No me cargues con tus problemas...{Don’t pass off all your work to someone else…}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.69,0:08:45.93,HnF,,0,0,0,,¡Por favor! ¡Dejaré que hagas lo que quieras con tus tetas!{Please! I’ll let you do whatever you like with your boobs!}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.19,0:08:49.88,HnF,,0,0,0,,En primer lugar, mis tetas ya son mías,{In the first place, my boobs are already mine,}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.88,0:08:53.95,HnF,,0,0,0,,pero como sea. Es por Karen, al fin y al cabo.{but whatever. It’s for Karen-chan, after all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.28,0:08:57.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Lo primero que quiero escuchar\N es tu opinión al respecto.{First off I’d like to hear what you think about the whole thing.}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.28,0:09:02.12,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿Estás de acuerdo con Karen, o con sus amigos?{Do you support Karen-chan or her other colleagues?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.49,0:09:04.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Con Karen, sin lugar a duda.{That would be Karen-chan, of course.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.56,0:09:09.44,HnF,,0,0,0,,Es terrible pensar en quitarse de encima un árbol que sigue vivo, sin una razón justificable.{It’s terrible to think of getting rid of a tree that’s still living, without any justifiable reason.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.39,0:09:16.74,HnF,,0,0,0,,Si me preguntas por qué nadie ha logrado darse cuenta de su existencia hasta ahora,{If you asked me why nobody managed to notice that tree’s existence until now,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.74,0:09:23.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,más que darse cuenta o no,\N es solo que no eran conscientes de eso.{rather than noticing or not noticing, it’s just that nobody was really conscious of it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.04,0:09:27.04,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero cuando te das cuenta por un momento, no puedes para de verlo.{But when you notice it for just a moment, then you can’t help but really notice it.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.04,0:09:30.15,HnF,,0,0,0,,Y te llamará más la atención de lo normal.{And it’ll be more noticeable in your eyes than it needs to be.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.72,0:09:34.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,Cuando aprendes una palabra nueva \N y la ves en una frase,{When you learn a new word, and you see that word in a sentence,}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.38,0:09:38.20,HnF,,0,0,0,,parece que esa palabra destaca más, ¿no?{that word seems to stand out more. Something like that, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.65,0:09:41.18,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sí, supongo que sí.{Right. Well, I wonder.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.18,0:09:43.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,Me gustaría confirmar algo, Araragi.{I’d like to confirm something, Araragi-kun.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.20,0:09:48.95,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ahora mismo, en ese dojo, \Nla situación es de pánico general, ¿no?{Right now, at that dojo, the situation is a pandemic-like panic, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:56.12,HnF,,0,0,0,,'Pánico' me parece exagerado... \NPero supongo que sí está extendido.{Panic is kind of an exaggerated word… But I suppose it is kind of like a mass infection.}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.67,0:09:59.57,HnF,,0,0,0,,Entonces, solo tienes que acabar con eso.{Then, you just need to bring that to an end.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.42,0:10:02.83,HnF,,0,0,0,,Bueno, eso es verdad.{Well, that’s true.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.83,0:10:08.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero es difícil mantener en jaque\N una pandemia, ¿no es así?{But it’s hard to keep a pandemic in check, isn’t it? That’s what’s troublesome.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.80,0:10:12.50,HnF,,0,0,0,,No, hay una forma. \NUn método para detener la pandemia.{No, there’s a way. A way to stop a pandemic.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.29,0:10:18.01,HnF,,0,0,0,,Más que un método para detenerla, \Nes un método para que se detenga por sí misma.{Rather than a way to stop it, it’s more like a way for it to stop on its own.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.42,0:10:19.84,HnF,,0,0,0,,No tengo más remedio esta vez.{I guess I have no choice this time.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.09,0:10:24.81,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Y ahora para el epílogo, o mejor, la conclusión.{And now for the epilogue, or rather, the punch line.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.47,0:10:31.02,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Para empezar, el árbol que Karen estaba intentando proteger, no fue talado.{To start with the conclusion, the old tree that Karen was trying to protect was, in the end, not chopped down.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.72,0:10:38.97,HnF,,0,0,0,,Para poder hacer que el pánico se detenga,\N tiene que llegar a su destino, entonces se detendrá.{In order for a pandemic or a panic to stop, it has to arrive at its destination, then it will stop.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.62,0:10:44.99,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,No importa que virus sea, \Nsi se esparce hasta que no pueda más,{In short, no matter the virus, once it spreads until it can’t spread any further,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:51.35,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,la infección se parará\N y la situación llegará por sí misma a una solución.{the infection will stop, and the situation will naturally begin to resolve itself.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.32,0:10:56.26,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Pero está bastante claro \Nque no podemos dejar que llegue a su destino.{But it was pretty clear that we couldn't actually let arrive at its destination.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.02,0:10:59.30,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Si la pandemia continúa hasta su destino,{If this pandemic was made to continue to its ‘destination’,}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.30,0:11:02.70,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,el resultado será la muerte del árbol.{then the result would be the disposal of that old tree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.67,0:11:07.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Por eso mismo, podemos simplemente cambiarlo.{That’s why, we can simply shift the goal.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.17,0:11:12.73,HnF,,0,0,0,,Justo ahora, todos creen que el árbol es algo 'extraño', ¿no?{Right now, everyone thinks that the tree is on the 'ominous’ level, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.73,0:11:17.99,HnF,,0,0,0,,O, posiblemente, todos piensen en él como algo 'siniestro'.{Or, possibly, a level above at 'scary' it has up to that level of recognition, right?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.60,0:11:24.92,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo tenemos que llevarlo un paso más allá.\N Ese será su destino.{We just need to take it a step further. That will be the goal.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.89,0:11:27.17,HnF,,0,0,0,,Un paso más...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.99,0:11:29.94,HnF,,0,0,0,,Ese sería veneración, ¿no crees?{That would be reverence, wouldn’t it?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.13,0:11:35.54,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,El día siguiente, Karen hizo un anuncio al resto de estudiantes del dojo.{The next day, Karen told all the other dojo students this:}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.54,0:11:40.47,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,El árbol es de la misma madera \Ncon la que se construyó el dojo sagrado.{That old tree was made of the same wood as what was used to build the sacred dojo.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.47,0:11:45.22,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Parece que el dios que protege el dojo \Nhizo que creciese en el patio.{So it seems that the god that protected the dojo made the tree grow in the backyard.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.63,0:11:48.61,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Por eso ha ocurrido ese fenómeno tan extraño.{That’s why such a bizarre phenomenon occurred.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.56,0:11:50.85,HnF,,0,0,0,,El dios de las artes marciales,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.85,0:11:56.27,HnF,,0,0,0,,que ha estado protegiendo este dojo, ocultando su presencia durante décadas,{The god of martial arts, who has been watching over this dojo while hiding its presence for decades,}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.27,0:11:59.90,HnF,,0,0,0,,usó toda su fuerza para aparecer.{used all its strength to make an appearance.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.90,0:12:02.68,HnF,,0,0,0,,Sería irrespetuoso talarlo.{It would be outrageous to chop this tree down.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.37,0:12:07.87,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Ese engaño creado por Hanekawa fue tomado al pie de la letra,{This fabrication that Hanekawa came up with was adopted almost word for word.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.64,0:12:12.12,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Siendo eso cierto, no hay manera  que piensen en herir al árbol.{With the truth being what it is, there’s no way they’d think to hurt the tree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.68,0:12:17.54,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Por supuesto, esta no sería suficiente para engañar al maestro de Karen.{Of course, this wasn’t a lie meant to fool Karen’s master.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.48,0:12:20.71,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Si lo piensas bien,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.71,0:12:25.48,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,es prácticamente imposible que la madera de ese árbol sea la misma que se usó para construir el dojo.{If you considered it normally, there was no way the wood used to build the dojo was the same as that old tree.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.32,0:12:30.56,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero el maestro probablemente no se quejará.{But, the master probably won’t point that out.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.56,0:12:34.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,Como se esperaba, Karen se las arregló para persuadir a los demás.{As promised, Karen-chan did manage to persuade the others, after all.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.61,0:12:40.61,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Por ahora, la vida de ese árbol está a salvo.{For now, that old tree’s life was tethered.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.61,0:12:45.39,HnF_Pensa,,0,0,0,,Karen, siendo la que 'descubrió' el árbol, \Ntomó la responsabilidad de protegerlo hasta el final.{Karen, having been the one to 'discover’ the tree, took the responsibility of protecting it to the end.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.40,0:12:51.38,HnF,,0,0,0,,Pero aun así, mentir sienta mal.{But no matter what, telling a lie makes you feel bad…}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.92,0:12:53.54,HnF,,0,0,0,,Aunque no es necesariamente una mentira...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.36,0:12:59.42,HnF,,0,0,0,,Existe la posibilidad de que el árbol sea realmente un excentricidad.{It’s possible that that tree could actually have been an oddity.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.85,0:13:05.80,HnF,,0,0,0,,En primer lugar, no es completamente imposible que sea de la misma madera que el dojo.{In the first place, it’s not like it’s completely impossible for it to be the same wood used to build the dojo.}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.32,0:13:08.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,La posibilidad no es cero.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.62,0:13:13.06,HnF,,0,0,0,,¿De qué estás hablando?\N La posibilidad sigue siendo ínfima.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.82,0:13:17.77,HnF,,0,0,0,,Solo por que sea ínfima, \Nno significa que sea despreciable.{Just because it’s low, doesn’t mean it’s not possible,}
